SIMPLE: facile
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Facile
<hw>Fac"ile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>facilis</ets>,
prop., capable of being done or made, hence, facile, easy, fr.
<ets>facere</ets> to make, do: cf. F. <ets>facile</ets>. Srr
<er>Fact</er>, and cf. <er>Faculty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Easy to
be done or performed: not difficult; performable or attainable with
little labor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Order . . . will render the work <qex>facile</qex> and
delightful.</q> <rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Easy to be surmounted or removed; easily
conquerable; readily mastered.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>facile</qex> gates of hell too slightly barred.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Easy of access or converse; mild; courteous; not
haughty, austere, or distant; affable; complaisant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I meant she should be courteous, <qex>facile</qex>, sweet.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Easily persuaded to good or bad; yielding; ductile
to a fault; pliant; flexible.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Since Adam, and his <qex>facile</qex> consort Eve,⟦br⟧
Lost Paradise, deceived by me.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is treating Burns like a child, a person of so
<qex>facile</qex> a disposition as not to be trusted without a keeper on
the king's highway.</q> <rj><qau>Prof. Wilson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Ready; quick; expert; <as>as, he is <ex>facile</ex>
in expedients; he wields a <ex>facile</ex> pen.</as></def></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Fac"ile*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Fac"ile*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Facilitate</ent>⟦br⟧
